        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-03-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-03-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="1082" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1082">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363/3–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-02T09:00:00+07:00">March 2, 1945—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>342. ReDeptel 310, February 23, 5 p.m. Regarding American petroleum experts now
                    enroute to China, Coonley, Taelsons [<hi rend="italic">Nelson’s?</hi>] deputy
                    here, states complete Chinese National Government and Provincial Government
                    cooperation already assured through prior arrangements made by him with Dr.
                    Soong and Dr. Wong Wen-hao, chairman of Chinese WPB, and no further action
                    necessary at present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
